caller_intent: The caller (Tracy) is informing the client that Auto Owners lifted a non-renewal on their current policy but clarifying that the client has already secured a cheaper auto insurance policy through National General. The client wants to cancel the Auto Owners policy and confirm the effective date of the new policy.
resolution_steps: Tracy acknowledges the client's cancellation request and confirms the effective date of the new policy (yesterday).
Tracy offers to send a cancellation form to the client for signing to process the Auto Owners policy cancellation.
Tracy agrees to investigate the rate discrepancy between the quoted rate (from Alliance) and the rate the client secured through National General.
knowledge_required: Rate discrepancy resolution processes with carriers
summary: Tracy from Alliance Insurance discusses a client's request to cancel an Auto Owners policy after securing a cheaper rate through National General. Tracy confirms the effective date of the new policy, offers to send a cancellation form, and agrees to investigate the rate discrepancy. The client retains their homeowners policy but cancels the auto insurance.
